 </code></b></td></tr><tr><td class="number">3</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><b><code>represented in the General Assembly:</code></b><code>
  </code><code>
 </code><br>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td class="number">4</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>Section 1. </code><code>Short title. </code><code>This Act may be cited as the </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">5</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>Community Bank of Illinois Act.</code><br>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td class="number">6</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>Section 5. </code><code>Purpose.</code><code> For the purpose of
encouraging and </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">7</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>promoting agriculture, commerce, and industry, the State shall
</code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">8</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>engage in the business of banking, and for that purpose shall </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">9</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>maintain a system of banking
